so that won't be an issue. However, I'm unsure if Native Image can actually load classes already in the image using `URLClassLoader`. It might not work and could lead to an error, so I’ll need to think through the dynamic class loading patterns carefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing options**\\n\\nI’m thinking that maybe I won't need to run any tests. I could look into using `git diff` instead to check for changes. This might help me see what modifications have been made without diving deep into running tests right away. Hm, I wonder if this will be sufficient for the task at hand—I'm just trying to streamline the process and not overcomplicate things. Let's see how this goes!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XVMnzTART3LD5OYHURf4cL3e|fc_032442406b9b196e0169f551f8e5ac819f8a4ae9b15c94c23d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/test/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"git diff -- tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/test/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1605, "output": 1624, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34461, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777684959407, "responseId": "resp_032442406b9b196e0169f551e0125c819fbc6244c8922bd13e"}}
