[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test configurations**\n\nI'm thinking about the coverage agent and whether it's functioning correctly with the child context. It seems that dynamic access reports might not be applicable here, along with possibly reaching the agent during test execution.\n\nI wonder if I can use an upstream system property to specify the test runtime classpath. Leveraging a null parent for isolated class loading could be a solution, but the system loader still holds the library. Maybe removing google-collections from the system class loader is just not feasible.\n\n**Evaluating classloader issues**\n\nI'm thinking about the situation where if the SystemLoader can't find the Finalizer, then the DecoupledLoader might handle it. However, the report indicates that the new FRQ didn't cover this issue since it used the default test classloader, which could allow the system loader to load. But I'm concerned that an isolated classloader might change this scenario somehow. It's a bit confusing, and I want to ensure I'm understanding it correctly!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_032442406b9b196e0169f5525b1d38819f934af89afe32ba30\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9VJySmCQ8plngB3kQXoGdCXAbzCVaT7uL1RB7KuceIyOtonKX0zh2ZwBau7pkVvr7nQoJxRjJl1bumwh9bjqmU33Q_ra8Rw5RA-udRhvYDtPcEhTPB2sNgp-RAjosLqv1sRZSOEGfnbsGkZPWT96a0hsu4IxzavObDV0qyOIZ64jP9aVUB_S3vAcuF7PwjMeDhdeumy0FXE3Jk0WMN1ReS9k8yX33-70QUD7c2S9F7VEmL4dZSoKohxsAAfCH6ww0KClK5_mlDD8_NkMEjxok4BJxoCKt1icXdfYZXosQ7mpJbLQbgV003av7Oe7eMG22KeaxTjnNgIIxcfQ6blLIT03VWu6qCMifiEp5ZTZbkW-u_E4n7EVIm6tSa9F2AJ5NdOczX7oi7obVPJJ6bcxfOci23SKI76xpRc7gLAibfVGV-FD2tJHq2vmloWgMPLRMSO9lZvV4qXdAC49UmYAVR7LEZEft6DiXbCq92w9Ei5g6DOUtw-v4mgZmwJRPT1a7msbhSkZSaldfy_NgqT8qpCk4R-1AoID91rkuDwJC2HbPlsQoVO_3Vtqo5_9uWm00fxkT8nCdmL16de3etGhEDdxncwh8QvJmdmh76I5KlZ9Wc5jE2AAPSFaBt1U5nfuT1MZcWKgHg2iJpo72C5CbFmfvxAjHFA-v22rGy-H-pyD33kv1selDpjdg