C9t-jhUPGVZbuqGTNgblYU2h0UFsVHJA33oQWjM\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring classloader options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about modifying the test runtime classpath to prevent the system classloader from loading Google Collections, but it seems that dependency is necessary for the tests. In Gradle, I wonder if the system classloader is responsible for loading tests or dependencies. With JDK9 and above, it appears the system classloader is the app loader. Using Gradle to fork tests in a separate JVM might be tricky, especially regarding coverage. Maybe a subprocess could work, but I’m not sure if it would track everything effectively. A custom Java agent could help, but there are limitations, like needing adjustments at JVM start.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering custom classloaders**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to implement a custom classloader in Java tests. The custom class must be on the classpath and have a ClassLoader constructor. However, if I set this for all tests, the library's SystemLoader might face issues loading classes, particularly the finalizer. Perhaps I could implement the custom classloader directly in the test source, using `java.system.class.loader` to reference it. At JVM startup, this custom loader needs to be loaded by the built-in app loader, as the test classes will be part of the classpath.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the implications of using `loadClass` for the finalizer. If the system loader loads Google collections for regular tests, it could cause issues with the Finalizer not loading. I wonder if using a DecoupledLoader would handle existing `FinalizerTest`. But could this affect all tests? For a native image, I realize the system property won’t apply. I might need to introduce a helper class like `FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader`, but that could violate the one-to-one principle. Would a public static nested class work instead?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loader requirements**\\n\\nI'm considering how the property class name could be binary with a `$`, but it shouldn't be the test name. It needs to be loaded by the app loader, which might mean a nested static class is suitable. However, using it like `com...FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest$FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader` might break rules about test class names. I should think about creating a separate top-level class, and it seems only public top-level classes are allowed. I’m also wondering if using reflection with a public constructor is necessary, or if I could set the JVM argument instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing class and file naming**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the naming approach for files and tests. It looks like the actual runtime class can include a `$`, even if the user specifies not to use it in test class or file names. While it's probably okay to avoid using `$` in file names, I’m concerned about how a custom system classloader might react. If it rejects the finalizer, the DecoupledLoader would create a URLClassLoader with the parent system loader, which adds complexity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dx56ikKTzvFHr7LOrh9OhIUN|fc_032442406b9b196e0169f5539a8064819f871bc377319d22e4", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/test/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_collections.google_collections;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.common.base.FinalizableReferenceQueue;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest {\n    private static final String FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"com.google.common.base.internal.Finalizer\";\n\n    @Test\n    void finalizableReferenceQueueUsesDecoupledLoaderWhenSystemLoaderCannotLoadFinalizer() {\n        try {\n            FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader.reset();\n\n            FinalizableReferenceQueue queue = new FinalizableReferenceQueue();\n\n            assertThat(queue).isNotNull();\n            if (ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader() instanceof FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader) {\n                assertThat(FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader.rejectedFinalizerLookup()).isTrue();\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static volatile boolean rejectedFinalizerLookup;\n\n        public FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                rejectedFinalizerLookup = true;\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name);\n        }\n\n        private static void reset() {\n            rejectedFinalizerLookup = false;\n        }\n\n        private static boolean rejectedFinalizerLookup() {\n            return rejectedFinalizerLookup;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/test/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_google_collections.google_collections;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport com.google.common.base.FinalizableReferenceQueue;\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest {\\n    private static final String FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME =\\n            \\\"com.google.common.base.internal.Finalizer\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void finalizableReferenceQueueUsesDecoupledLoaderWhenSystemLoaderCannotLoadFinalizer() {\\n        try {\\n            FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader.reset();\\n\\n            FinalizableReferenceQueue queue = new FinalizableReferenceQueue();\\n\\n            assertThat(queue).isNotNull();\\n            if (ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader() instanceof FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader) {\\n                assertThat(FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader.rejectedFinalizerLookup()).isTrue();\\n            }\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n        private static volatile boolean rejectedFinalizerLookup;\\n\\n        public FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\\n            super(parent);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            if (FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\\n                rejectedFinalizerLookup = true;\\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\\n            }\\n            return super.loadClass(name);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static void reset() {\\n            rejectedFinalizerLookup = false;\\n        }\\n\\n        private static boolean rejectedFinalizerLookup() {\\n            return rejectedFinalizerLookup;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1463, "output": 3016, "cacheRead": 48640, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53119, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777685368796, "responseId": "resp_032442406b9b196e0169f5537a6f20819f855bd01a49887c19"}}
