[assistant] Fixed the Jacoco/javaagent crash caused by the custom system class loader.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - When `java.system.class.loader` is set, the JVM instrumentation agent expects the system class loader to define `appendToClassPathForInstrumentation(String)`.
[assistant] - Our custom loader did not, so Jacoco failed during JVM startup.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Updated `tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/testSystemClassLoader/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader.java`
[assistant]   - It now extends `URLClassLoader`.
[assistant]   - It defines `appendToClassPathForInstrumentation(String path)`.
[assistant]   - That method appends the agent JAR path via `addURL(...)`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] This preserves the intended behavior of hiding only `com.google.common.base.internal.Finalizer` from the system loader, while allowing Jacoco’s agent setup to complete.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test command.
[assistant-event] text_end
